    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab><note>Il <rs key="#Princeps">principe</rs>
                            <persName key="#Princeps" ref="#people/303">Arechi II</persName> offre
                            al monastero di S. Sofia di <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/110"
                                >Benevento</placeName> (prosegue l'elenco iniziato con il doc.
                            3535):</note></ab> <ab>(…) [57] Nec non et ex <geogName ref="#estates/3407" key="#Gai #Fiscal_property"><placeName
                                key="#Uncertain_tradition #Villages/settlements #Gai #Fiscal_property #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                                ref="#places/3417"><rs key="#Gai">gaio</rs> nostro
                            Scla</placeName></geogName> largimus predicto <orgName
                            key="#Wood #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/85">Sancte Sophię <rs key="#Monasteries"
                                >monasterio</rs></orgName> ad <rs
                            key="#Wood #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                            >ligna</rs> faciendum annualiter in eo loco in quo aptus fuerit ad
                        nominata ligna trahendum. (…)</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p><emph>Editions</emph>: IS1 VIII, col. 581A; IS2 VIII, coll. 32B; IS2 X-2, col.
                    428B; Borgia 1769, I, pp. 296-297; Cappelletti 1845, p. 43; CSS, I, 1 [57], pp.
                    329-330 (source of the text reproduced here). <emph>Document summaries</emph>:
                    Di Meo 1795-1819, III, p. 97; Bertolini O, 1926, 72; RIM, 451.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="additional">
                <p/>
            </div>
